Package: simaltruist
Type: Package
Title: Altruistic Behavior in Animal Populations
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Homer", "White",
           email = "homerhanumat@gmail.com", 
           role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Sara", "Sandman", 
           email = "ssandman@georgetowncollege.edu", 
           role = c("aut")))
Maintainer: Homer White <homerhanumat@gmail.com>
Description: For use by students and colleagues in evolutionary biology.
    Simulates an animal population under recurrent attack by predators.
    Some individuals have altruistic genes.  The user can write custom
    functions to govern mate-selection and behavior of altruists during
    an attack.
Imports:
    dplyr,
    ggplot2,
    igraph
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://github.com/homerhanumat/simaltruist
NeedsCompilation: no
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
